\subsection*{Code availability}
All code used in the present study is provided under the GNU General Public Licence alongside the resulting datasets (see Data Records section). Spatial input data was processed in GRASS GIS. The R package \textit{randomForest}, which provides an interface to the original Fortran code \cite{breiman_random_2001}, was used for statistical analysis. Land change modelling was carried out using the \textit{lulcc} software package \cite{moulds_open_2015}. The implementation of HILDA is adapted from the original model description \cite{fuchs_high-resolution_2013}. The version of \textit{lulcc} used in the present study is provided in the data repository; in addition, a development version resides on the first author's GitHub account (\url{https://github.com/simonmoulds/r_lulcc2}). \\

